<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-01-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-01-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="390" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to <gloss type="to">Emperor of Germany</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Executive Mansion</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-01-10"><hi rend="italic">January 10,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I am much gratified at Your Majesty’s purpose to send your yacht <hi rend="italic">Hohenzollern</hi> to be present at the christening of
                            your new yacht by my daughter, and I assure you of a hearty welcome for
                            your brother, Admiral Prince Henry, to whom I can personally express my
                            cordial feelings of esteem for Your Majesty and my earnest wishes for
                            the prosperity of the German people.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore
                            Roosevelt</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>